1. create a .txt file containing all accession number of the desired dataset
2. fast1-dump --split (see code in viralrecon, loop is used)
3. Compress al fastq files to save space using gunzip
4. there is a python script that uses data to create a CSV sample sheet automatically:

wget -L https://raw.githubusercontent.com/nf-core/viralrecon/master/bin/fastq_dir_to_samplesheet.py

Run the script using the following command:

 python3 fastq_dir_to_samplesheet.py data samplesheet.csv -r1 _1.fastq.gz -r2 _2.fastq.gz

 Samplesheet.csv is ready to be used in viralrecon.

 5. conda activate nextflow

 
